{"word":"ἐμφορέω","slug":"ἐμφορέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐμφορέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>= <a href='S:ἐμφέρω'><el>ἐμφέρω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be borne about in</i> or <i>on</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to pour in</i>, <el>ἄκρατον</el> <b>Diod.</b>:— <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> and <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to take one's fill</i> or <i>make much use of</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to put upon, inflict on</i>, <el>ἐμφορεῖν πληγάς τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to object to, throw in one's teeth</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}